Title: What's a trusted setup? What's a Structured Reference String? What's toxic waste?
Description:
In proof systems, provers and the verifiers rely on a common set of parameters,  sometimes referred to as the common reference string (CRS).
In some proof systems (for example, the ones that rely on pairings) a dangerous setup phase produces these common parameters. Dangerous because it generates random values, encrypts them, and then must get rid of the random values so that no one can ever find  ...
